definition: permanent tooth (as opposed to deciduous tooth 乳牙)/adult tooth
permanent/constant/fixed/usual/ordinary/rule (old)/one of the 64 hexagrams of the Book of Changes (䷟)

sentences.english: Conclusion The antibiotic cataplasm had a good effect on young permanent teeth with periapical periodontitis.
sentences.chinese: 结论抗生素糊剂对于年轻恒牙根尖周炎具有良好效果。

sentences.english: You wished for your child to have all permanent teeth.
sentences.chinese: 你多希望孩子的牙都换成了恒牙。

sentences.english: Objective To observe the effect of pulpotomy in treatment of juvenile permanent teeth lesion.
sentences.chinese: 目的观察活髓切断术在青少年恒牙治疗中临床疗效。

sentences.english: However, the primary teeth that are absent of permanent successor will produce root re-sorption and eventually exfoliate.
sentences.chinese: 恒牙胚缺失的乳牙也会发生根吸收，导致乳牙脱落。

sentences.english: It could interfere with the correct development of permanent teeth.
sentences.chinese: 吮吸拇指可能会妨碍恒牙的正常生长。

sentences.english: As these teeth fall out . Our permanent teeth come through.
sentences.chinese: 等乳牙脱落后，恒牙开始生长。

sentences.english: Objective To explore the influence of the deciduous lower front fused teeth on the succedaneous fixed teeth.
sentences.chinese: 目的探讨乳下前牙融合牙对恒牙的影响。

sentences.english: Conclusion The deciduous lower front fused teeth can influence the succedaneous fixed teeth and secondary dentition.
sentences.chinese: 结论乳下前牙融合牙对继承恒牙及恒牙列均有影响。

sentences.english: Conclusion The deciduous lower front fused teeth can influence the succedaneous fixed teeth and secondary dentition.
sentences.chinese: 结论乳下前牙融合牙对继承恒牙及恒牙列均有影响。

sentences.english: Only one, who looked a few years older than the rest, showed two new adult teeth at the top of his mouth.
sentences.chinese: 惟有一个较其余年长几岁的，门牙处长着两颗恒牙。

sentences.english: The eruption of permanent teeth have a certain amount of time and sequence.
sentences.chinese: 恒牙的萌出有一定的时间和次序。

definition: to grow replacement teeth (zoology)/to grow permanent teeth in place of milk teeth
caries/rotten tooth (colloquial)/see also 齲齒|龋齿[qu3 chi3]
